This is an agricultural and horticultural pest species, widely distributed on both coasts in New Caledonia , where it has spread via roadways into valleys in the Central Range. There are still nomenclatural issues with this taxon (
Li 1993
). Host plants are Solanaceae , including cultivated, weedy and wild species. This phytophagous ladybug has been recorded from Australia , Papua New Guinea (including New Britain and New Ireland ), Solomon Islands , Fiji Islands , Samoa , Philippines and Vietnam .
